  + [purpose] is compare finite Euler products and logarithmic-derivative prime-power weighting against zeta(s) and -zeta'(s)/zeta(s) in Re(s) > 1
  + [not_purpose] is RH proof, disproof, critical-line certification, independent zero certification, or theorem-level convergence authority

  = must: require sigma greater than 1 for Euler-product and Dirichlet-series convergence
  = must: compute finite product over primes p <= bound for requested sample points s = sigma + it
  = must: compute truncated prime-factor logarithmic derivative over primes p <= bound
  = must: compute finite prime-power/von-Mangoldt cutoff over p^k <= bound
  = must: compare each finite surface to numerical zeta(s) and -zeta'(s)/zeta(s)
  = must: expose residual magnitudes and included prime/prime-power counts
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_euler_product_log_derivative_probe_not_rh_evidence
  - never: use Euler-product convergence in Re(s) > 1 as direct RH evidence
  - never: claim zero-line behavior from finite product or logarithmic-derivative traces

